 {"id":"bd-87bp2","title":"N1: Cranelift IR lowering for INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE VDBE programs","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-31T19:16:18.136147563Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T04:40:26.058667654Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":3387,"issue_id":"bd-87bp2","author":"ubuntu","text":"## What
Translate VDBE programs for INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE into Cranelift IR. Each opcode becomes one or more Cranelift instructions:
- Integer/String8/Null → immediate loads
- MakeRecord → inline serialization code (no function call)
- Insert → direct call to B-tree insert API
- SeekRowid → direct call to cursor seek
- Comparison → native cmp + branch

## Where
- New file: crates/fsqlite-vdbe/src/jit.rs
- Integration: crates/fsqlite-vdbe/src/engine.rs — before execute loop, check if JIT version exists
- Crate dep: cranelift-codegen, cranelift-frontend, cranelift-module

## Scope: Only INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE with no subqueries, no triggers, no RETURNING
Complex queries remain interpreted. This covers the hot path that matters most.

## Acceptance Criteria
1. JIT-compiled INSERT matches interpreted INSERT results (proptest)
2. INSERT benchmark: ≥ 15% faster for repeated prepared statements
3. JIT compilation time: < 1 ms per statement (amortized over 3+ executions)
4. No unsafe code in JIT bridge (Cranelift manages the native code)
